    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/frank_miller_482111",
        "quote": "I thought Daredevil was kind of cool because he couldn't do anything. I mean, he's blind. It wasn't that he could fly. His major power was an impediment. So I was intrigued. When I took over he was kind of like Spider-Man-lite, but I was able to project a lot of my Catholic imagery onto it. And I'd always wanted to do a crime comic.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Frank Miller",
            "url": "/quotes/frank_miller_482111"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thought",
                "url": "/topics/thought"
